
[1]certainty

   CERTAINTY, n.

   1. A fixed or real state; truth; fact.

   Know for a certainty, that the Lord your God will no more drive out
   these nations. Josh. 23. Luke 1.

   2. Full assurance of mind; exemption from doubt.

   Certainty is the perception of the agreement or disagreement of our
   ideas.

   3. Exemption from failure; as the certainty of an event, or of the
   success of a medicine.

   The certainty of punishment is the truest security against crimes.

   4. Regularity; settled state.
